<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">839.51/3417</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                    <gloss type="to">Lee, Higginson &amp;
                            Company</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-16">June 16, 1931</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sirs</hi>: The Department has received your letter
                            of June 9 regarding Dominican financing. The Department is giving the
                            matter careful consideration and, in this connection, would like to be
                            advised more fully what you have in mind regarding a refunding loan
                            mentioned in paragraph (7) on page 7 of your letter under
                            acknowledgement.</p>
                        <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis
                                    White</hi></signed><lb/><hi rend="italic">Assistant
                                Secretary</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>